<|startoftext|>The staff always greets me with a smile as I walk in the door. The baristas and staff are friendly, and the prices are fair! For a drink and the chance to meet a friend, this is what you get, a coffee bar in a big plaza!<|endoftext|>
<|startoftext|>I went in in last Saturday and looked around. There is no real sense in going back in without having your tires fixed. They didn't work that night. I sent in a comment about my tire and was told they couldn't fix them. I asked why and was told it was an OEM problem, I had one replaced when I had a bad flat tire two days earlier. After that the rear tire had a pinched or yellowed sidewall from not replaced that week...and it cost me double to fix them. I sent a report and will not be back even if I can get a discount there. In fact, I recommend not going there at all. They have the worst staff here! I will be back when my tires look like new!<|endoftext|>
<|startoftext|>I love this place! I've been here about a dozen times now and it gets pretty packed during lunch. There is so much stuff to grab, no matter who you come with. It's so clean and organized. I love how you could order one of whatever the items are and choose from a menu of about 20 options. I always get the chipotle chili ranch dressing. Yum!<|endoftext|>
<|startoftext|>This place was one of our favorite things on Vegas vacation. We went here on a Thursday night around 5:00 pm. Not much seating, I guess. It's been closed for over a year. I sat at the bar, so there were three other people in our group and we were able to order food fairly fast.\n\nThey had a menu of a couple drinks and appetizers and then we started off with the appetizers. I got a beef salad with roasted greens and poutines. My mother got a steak salad with mushrooms, and I got a chicken salad with a little bit of veggies, a fried sweet potato roll, and then I was taken out to dinner.\n\nFood was served piping hot, so I don't know how the food was prepared. However, the service was so fantastic and so friendly. I will be back and I hope everyone can eat here sometime. It's the best food I've tried in Vegas which is a good sign. We'll be back for sure!<|endoftext|>
<|startoftext|>I'm a huge fan of their desserts. I love the frosting, it's just like what you would get at a candy store. And the cookie it was on tasted way better than the original that I got. \nThey also have a large variety of things. I was trying to look forward to going there but all my friends and family told me why they were there; it's the most fun they've had eating there in ages. They've got all kinds of fun items!\nI really like the drinks here. There's a huge variety of alcohol and most of us have tried their drinks at some point.\nI would love to go out of my way to visit this place. It is definitely a must do!<|endoftext|>
<|startoftext|>Took a friend there for their birthday before our big trip to Vegas. This place was surprisingly empty. We were there from 11:30 pm-1:00 am. Parking is a little tricky. Parking at some of the other valet places (like Acela) will take you over an hour.<|endoftext|>
